Analysis Document 
Project Name: Digital Detective Mystery Game 

1.1 Project Overview 
During Week 1, the Digital Detective Mystery Game was conceptualized as a Java-based 
investigative game where the player solves crime cases using logic, evidence collection, and 
interrogation. 

1.2 Game Objectives 
□ Build a case-based detective investigation system 
□ Implement evidence collection and analysis system 
□ Create dialogue-based interrogation system 
□ Design structured case-solving gameplay 
□ Use Java OOP architecture for modular design 

1.3 Functional Requirements 
□ Investigation system (searching crime scenes) 
□ Evidence collection system 
□ Dialogue/interrogation system 
□ Case management system 
□ Suspect identification system 

1.4 Non-Functional Requirements 
□ Modular and maintainable OOP design 
□ Separate logic into independent classes 
□ Scalable case-based architecture 

1.5 Technology Selection 
□ Programming Language: Java 
□ Architecture: Object-Oriented Programming  
□ Optional UI: JavaFX (not implemented in Week 1) 

